-- 172_ingredient_info_backfill_batch2.sql
-- Ingredient info backfill — batch 2 of the flavour/origin/season fill (Richard, 23.7.2026).
-- Same safety contract as db/171: ONLY fills fields that are currently empty (coalesce + nullif),
-- matched case-insensitively by name. It NEVER overwrites an existing value. Reference facts
-- (taste / where it comes from / season) are universal, so this fills every kitchen's copy of the
-- ingredient — price stays per-kitchen and untouched. Non-destructive: no deletes, no drops.
-- Covers the alphabetical range "00 Flour Or Strong Bread Flour" → "Beef Rump" (150 names).
